1) Incorrect assumption: settings-derived base_url is the full, request-visible prefix. Location: django/core/files/storage.py::FileSystemStorage.url. Evidence: code uses urljoin(self.base_url, url) with no call to get_script_prefix(). Relationship that should be used at call-time (preserved):
   if base.startswith('/') and not base.startswith('//'):
       script_prefix = get_script_prefix().rstrip('/')
       if script_prefix and not base.startswith(script_prefix + '/'):
           base = script_prefix + base
   return urljoin(base, url)

2) Incorrect assumption: template prefix tags may return raw settings.<name> as the site-visible prefix. Location: django/templatetags/static.py::PrefixNode.handle_simple. Evidence: handle_simple returns iri_to_uri(getattr(settings, name, '')) without script-prefix logic. Relationship to compute effective prefix (preserved):
   if prefix.startswith('/') and not prefix.startswith('//'):
       script_prefix = get_script_prefix().rstrip('/')
       if script_prefix and not prefix.startswith(script_prefix + '/'):
           prefix = script_prefix + prefix

3) Incorrect assumption: staticfiles post-processor (hashed/manifest) can match and slice using settings.STATIC_URL directly. Location: django/contrib/staticfiles/storage.py::HashedFilesMixin.url_converter. Evidence: code tests url.startswith(settings.STATIC_URL) and uses target_name = url_path[len(settings.STATIC_URL):]. Required relationships (preserved):
   static_prefix = settings.STATIC_URL
   if static_prefix.startswith('/') and not static_prefix.startswith('//'):
       script_prefix = get_script_prefix().rstrip('/')
       if script_prefix and not static_prefix.startswith(script_prefix + '/'):
           static_prefix = script_prefix + static_prefix
   (use static_prefix in startswith checks and slicing)
   assert url_path.startswith(static_prefix)
   target_name = url_path[len(static_prefix):]

4) Incorrect assumption: dev static handler matches request.path against raw settings.STATIC_URL path. Location: django/contrib/staticfiles/handlers.py::StaticFilesHandlerMixin.get_base_url (and caller comparisons). Evidence: get_base_url returns settings.STATIC_URL, later parsed path is compared to request.path with no script-prefix applied. Relationship to compute base used for path comparisons (preserved):
   if base.startswith('/') and not base.startswith('//'):
       script_prefix = get_script_prefix().rstrip('/')
       if script_prefix and not base.startswith(script_prefix + '/'):
           base = script_prefix + base
   return base

5) Incorrect assumption: django/conf/urls/static.static(prefix, ...) builds URL patterns from the raw prefix argument (commonly settings.MEDIA_URL). Location: django/conf/urls/static.py::static. Evidence: regex built from prefix.lstrip('/') will not match request paths that include a runtime script prefix. Relationship (preserved):
   if prefix.startswith('/') and not prefix.startswith('//'):
       script_prefix = get_script_prefix().rstrip('/')
       if script_prefix and not prefix.startswith(script_prefix + '/'):
           prefix = script_prefix + prefix
   (then build pattern as before)

6) Incorrect assumption encoded at storage initialization: StaticFilesStorage.__init__ sets base_url = settings.STATIC_URL at init time and treats that as sufficient for runtime URL generation. Location: django/contrib/staticfiles/storage.py::StaticFilesStorage.__init__ (and FileSystemStorage.base_url). Evidence: base_url cached at initialization from settings, but get_script_prefix() is request-local and must not be baked into a cross-request cache. Note: this identifies why script-prefix logic must be applied at call-time (storage.url()), not by mutating cached init-time base_url.

7) Incorrect assumption: template context processor exposing settings.STATIC_URL provides a request-visible prefix. Location: django/template/context_processors.py::static (context processor). Evidence: agent left this unchanged; it continues to expose the raw setting and therefore can mislead callers/tests that expect a script-aware STATIC_URL in templates.

8) Pattern-level issue / code audit gap: many call sites and third-party code directly reading settings.STATIC_URL or settings.MEDIA_URL are still wrong. Location: any code that uses settings.STATIC_URL/ MEDIA_URL for runtime URL generation, comparison, or slicing. Evidence: agent did not perform a full global audit; any direct usages that perform startswith checks or len() slicing against the raw setting will fail under a runtime script prefix.

